3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bybit calculates PENDLE/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using the premium index between perpetual and spot prices. Funding fees are exchanged directly between long and short position holders based on the 8-hour time-weighted average premium. The exchange applies a ±0.375% funding rate cap with automatic deleveraging protection for extreme market conditions."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","PENDLE","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"PENDLE's focus on yield tokenization creates predictable funding patterns around major DeFi protocol updates and yield farming seasons. The token's correlation with broader DeFi trends and relatively lower trading volumes compared to major cryptocurrencies can generate sustainable funding rate premiums for arbitrage strategies."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"PENDLE/USDT funding rates on Bybit typically range from -0.1% to +0.3% per 8-hour period, with higher positive rates during DeFi summer periods and protocol token launches. The pair shows strong correlation with Ethereum gas fees and DeFi TVL changes, creating predictable funding spikes during high network activity. Historical data indicates funding rates peak during major yield farming protocol integrations and Pendle V2 milestone announcements."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage between Bybit and other platforms often yields 0.05-0.15% per funding period due to PENDLE's mid-tier liquidity profile. The 8-hour funding interval provides sufficient time for position adjustments and risk management compared to platforms with more frequent settlements. Traders can capitalize on funding rate divergence during DeFi protocol governance events and yield strategy launches that affect PENDLE's utility demand."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"PENDLE's smaller market cap and DeFi sector volatility create higher liquidation risks during broader crypto market downturns or DeFi protocol exploits. The token's correlation with Ethereum ecosystem performance means funding arbitrage positions face systematic risk during network congestion or major protocol failures. Lower trading volumes compared to major cryptocurrencies can result in wider bid-ask spreads and increased slippage during position entry and exit."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What drives PENDLE funding rates on Bybit?","answer":"PENDLE funding rates are primarily driven by DeFi yield farming cycles, protocol adoption trends, and Ethereum ecosystem developments. Positive funding typically occurs during high DeFi activity periods when traders expect PENDLE price appreciation."},{"question":"How often are PENDLE funding fees settled on Bybit?","answer":"Bybit settles PENDLE/USDT funding fees every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. This 8-hour interval provides more time for arbitrage strategies compared to exchanges with hourly settlements."},{"question":"What are typical PENDLE funding rates on Bybit?","answer":"PENDLE funding rates typically range from -0.1% to +0.3% per 8-hour period, with rates often staying positive due to long bias from DeFi yield farming interest. Rates spike during major protocol updates and DeFi season periods."},{"question":"Is PENDLE suitable for funding rate arbitrage strategies?","answer":"PENDLE offers moderate arbitrage potential due to its mid-tier liquidity and DeFi-specific volatility patterns. The 8-hour funding interval and predictable rate patterns around DeFi events make it suitable for experienced arbitrage traders who understand yield farming cycles."}]}]
